-- Italy Leads Russia 2-0 After First Day of Fed Cup Tennis Final
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-11-02T18:39:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-02/italy-leads-russia-2-0-after-first-day-of-fed-cup-tennis-final.html
Roberta Vinci and Sara Errani won
singles matches to give  Italy  a 2-0 win over Russia in the Fed
Cup tennis final.  Vinci beat Alexandra Panova 5-7, 7-5, 8-6 in the opening
match in Cagliari. Errani followed with a 6-1, 6-4 win over
Alisa Kleybanova to move Italy within a victory of its third
title since 2009.  The best-of-five final in women’s tennis’s top team
competition concludes tomorrow with two reverse singles and a
doubles match.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  